---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is AN a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)" description="AN is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the indefinite article used before vowel sounds. Learn extensions and strategy tips." keywords="is an a scrabble word, an scrabble, an valid scrabble, an points scrabble, two letter a words, an meaning scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is AN a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)","description":"AN is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. Indefinite article before vowel sounds.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-an-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is AN a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, AN is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. It scores 2 points (A=1, N=1) and is the indefinite article used before words starting with a vowel sound."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you extend AN into?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AN extends into ANT (3pts), ANE (3pts), ANI (3pts), AND (4pts), ANY (6pts), ANGLE (6pts), ANKLE (9pts), and hundreds more. It's one of the most extensible 2-letter words."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is AN worth playing in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"AN is low-scoring at 2 points but extremely useful for parallel plays. Both A and N cross with nearly every letter, making AN perfect for laying alongside existing words to form multiple crosswords simultaneously."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is AN a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, AN is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's the indefinite article used before vowel sounds — "an apple," "an hour." While just 2 points, AN is a parallel-play powerhouse because both A and N form valid crosswords with nearly every letter on the board.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">AN</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · A=1, N=1 · Indefinite article</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL and SOWPODS. AN is one of the most common English words and one of the most useful 2-letter words for parallel plays. Both tiles are 1 point each, but the crossword potential is enormous.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9 A-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 N-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AN Extensions: Build From It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANT</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANI</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AND</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANY</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ANKLE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">AN Strategy: When to Play It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play king:</span> AN is arguably the best 2-letter word for parallel plays. A crosses with 23 letters and N crosses with many too. Place parallel to score from multiple crosswords.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Front hooks galore:</span> AN accepts BAN, CAN, DAN, FAN, MAN, PAN, RAN, TAN, VAN, WAN — 11 front hooks. Position AN carefully so opponents don't exploit it near premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Common tile combo:</span> With 9 A-tiles and 6 N-tiles in the bag, you'll often hold A+N together. Use AN for parallel scoring rather than waiting for longer words.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Did You Know?</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AN accepts <span class="text-white font-medium">more front hooks than almost any other 2-letter word</span>. BAN, CAN, DAN, FAN, MAN, NAN, PAN, RAN, TAN, VAN, WAN — that's 11 front hooks making board placement critical.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ad-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is AD a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 3 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-at-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is AT a Scrabble Word? Yes!</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
